Introduction

Triple H (Korean: 트리플 H; Japanese: トリプルH) was a co-ed subunit composed of HyunA and PENTAGON's Hui and E'Dawn under Cube Entertainment. They debuted on May 1, 2017 with their first mini album 199X.

The unit effectively disbanded following HyunA and E'Dawn's departure from Cube Entertainment in 2018.
